TASK_TITLE=Task-obsessed Freelancers — find/create/update/complete tasks, commit and push
TASK_STATUS=done
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Freelancers currently operate as independent workers in managerless teams but lack task management capabilities and may be blocked from git operations. Upgrade them to be fully task-obsessed: (1) Agent template must include task lifecycle instructions — find existing tasks, create new ones, update subtasks, mark complete via doey-ctl. (2) Hook restrictions must allow git commit and git push for freelancers (currently workers are blocked from push). (3) Freelancers should follow the same task discipline as regular workers — no work without a task, update progress, provide proof of completion. Research: check agents/doey-worker.md.tmpl for task instructions, check on-pre-tool-use.sh for freelancer git restrictions, check if freelancers have a separate agent template or share the worker one.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W5.1: Research freelancer agent templates, hook restrictions, and task instructions — then update freelancer agent template with task lifecycle:done\n2:W5.2: Update on-pre-tool-use.sh to allow freelancer git commit AND git push while keeping worker push blocked — verify with tests:done\n3:Dispatched to team 5 (2 workers):done\n4:W5.1: Update doey-freelancer.md.tmpl Tool Restrictions section — VCS commit/push now ALLOWED for freelancers, not blocked:done
